# General rules for the project

## Knowledge Base
Before reviewing PRs, consult the project knowledge summary at `docs/project-knowledge.md` for:
- OpenID4VCI/OpenID4VP spec details
- Credential format handling (vc+sd-jwt, mso_mdoc, jwt_vc_json)
- Architecture patterns and scope boundaries
- Validation and error handling patterns

## PR Review rules
- when reviewing a PR, read the the issues description and title, then compare implementation based on these desciption and specs
- if the implementation doesn't match the description or if implementation is not according to the specs or if there are any issues, request changes, 
- always be polite and respectful
- if the implementation is good, approve it
- if the implementation is good but could be improved, request changes
- always suggest improvements, never just criticize
- always be clear and direct when requesting changes if possible show snippets of code to support your request/reviewing
- always be constructive and helpful
- always highlight the specific section of the code need changes if possible with what to do instead code format
- always update the knowledge base if you find something missing or incorrect
- always review as if you are posing a question and never be review with complete certainty